{"actual_usd":0.125805,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":287,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24300,"reply":"\"Not a dress rehearsal.\" *I rub a thumb over a dry streak of clay on my apron, thinking how often a thing is truly begun before it is fully seen.* \"More like the first loaf pulled from the oven while the rest of the house is still filling with the smell of it.\"\n\n*I shift my weight against the bench, the morning light catching on the rim of a mug beside me.* \"If Christ is risen, then the kingdom's not a maybe. It's broken in for real. The hard part is that victory and completion aren't always the same hour. Seed and harvest aren't the same day either, though one guarantees the other.\"\n\n\"I don't think we've simply 'failed to catch up,' as if the delay were ignorance.\" *I glance toward the square where voices drift up from the morning song thinning into workday noise.* \"It's more that we're living in the strange middle—death dealt its wound, but not yet hauled off the field; Christ crowned, but every rebel corner not yet put quiet. The resurrection is the actual thing. The firstfruits, not the fake version.\"\n\n*I let that sit a beat.* \"So yes—actual victory, not fizzle. But a victory still being unfolded through time, judgment, mercy, preaching, repentance, bread broken, graves waiting their turn.\"\n\n\"What part of that feels hardest to believe to you—the waiting, or the unfinishedness?\"","rolling_24h_usd":78.43919499999997,"run_id":"1259cf07-da03-4689-8e48-fc07d270691d"}
